n \in \mathbb{N},
n+ (n-1) + \ldots 2 + 1 \;= \;1+2+\ldots+ (n-1) +n=\frac{n(n+1)}2
n = 12,\;
\;\dfrac{12(12+1)}2
\begin{array}{c} 1&+&2&+&3&+&\ldots&+&(n-1)&+&n&=&S\\ n&+&(n-1)&+&(n-2)&+&\ldots&+&2&+&1&=&S\\ \hline (n+1)&+&(n+1)&+&(n+1)&+&\ldots&+&(n+1)&+&(n+1)&=&2S \end{array}
n
n(n+1)=2S
